The paper deals with mechanism design, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The problem involves scheduling on a single machine, which is a classic problem in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses fairness and economic efficiency, which are topics in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper uses a probabilistic model for uncertainty, which is related to information theory (cs.IT).
